social_posts.post_text: November was a whirlwind! Between my birthday, events and work, one day blurred right into the next. I feel like I blinked and it was already December. Here’s a few fun moments from the past month. It’s the first time in awhile that I really felt like myself. 😊It’s taken me forever to put all these video clips together. I either have nothing to post or too much and then I get overwhelmed 😂 #byenovember #cameraroll #lifelately #momentsofmine

All of the lights 🤩 Spent some time this weekend wandering around and checking out the holiday decor. Here’s where I went so far: Hudson Yards, Columbus Circle, Radio City Music Hall and a beautiful townhouse on W51ST. I still have to make my way over to Rockefeller Center and Bryant Park. I went to 5th Ave last night and it was complete madness. I then got caught in a massive downpour. 😬 I’ll have to try again soon! Where’s your favorite place in the city during the holiday season? 🎄 #christmasinthecity #allofthelights #christmaslights #holidaydecor #hudsonyards

Thank you for being a friend 🎶 Last week I got to check out the Golden Girls Kitchen pop-up down in the Seaport District! I used to watch the show all the time and sometimes still do, so this was really fun to experience. Loved all the little details and of course, the 1980s Miami vibes! Stay golden 🍰 #goldengirls #nycpopup #staygolden #popup #goldengirlskitchen

December 4th marked 11 years since I first started my blog and began creating content here on social media. 11 years of sharing my life and building an incredible online community. I initially wasn’t going to post anything about it since my content has become more and more infrequent lately, but how could I not acknowledge something that has truly changed my life. ⁣I started my blog at a time when I was just beginning to navigate my grief. Losing my dad at 26 while simultaneously losing my job was extremely difficult for me to process. My life as I knew it would be forever changed.⁣
⁣
I turned to content as a creative outlet, which then led me down an incredible journey of working for myself. While it challenged me tremendously, it also gave me wonderful opportunities and brought me here to NYC, where I would live on my own for the first time. It helped me heal. It helped me grow. And it gave me the chance to connect with all of you. I’m forever grateful. ⁣
⁣
I’m in such a different place in my life at 39 than I was when I started this all at 28. Some of you have been here with me throughout all the extreme highs and all the intense lows — and I thank you for that. I thank you for always giving me the space to share my life with you and for feeling comfortable enough to share yours with me. I have so much love for you. 🫶🏼 Here’s a little walk down memory lane. Cheers to 11 years! 🥳 #anniversary #11years #mystory #lifechats #thankyou #myjourney⁣

Memories of Christmas past and a little New Year’s surprise at the end.❤️ This holiday season has flown by, as it always does. I didn’t get to do all the things I had hoped to, but I’ve been reminiscing on these moments from my camera roll. ⁣
⁣
The holidays are such a joyous time, but it can also be really difficult for some. I know for me personally these days can sometimes feel extra heavy. My grief likes to make sure that its presence is known. Sending extra love to anyone who might be struggling, especially this time of year. I hope you know you’re not alone and I hope you find lots of reasons to smile. ❤️ #christmasinnyc #holidayseason #christmaspast #theholidays #christmastime

Let’s go shopping! 🤩 I had such a fun morning at the @whbm store in Roosevelt Field Mall on Saturday. I loved their mix of holiday and spring styles. They have so many transitional pieces that can take you from work to happy hour or a holiday party. And they have some petite options too, including denim! #teamnohem⁣
⁣
The employees were all wonderful and so helpful. They have a stylist in-store that can help you put looks together and share style tips. There’s a bunch of sales going on right now too! You also have the option to buy online and pick-up in-store or curbside.⁣
⁣
Which pieces would you most likely try on? I was obsessed with the sparkly booties (Vegan Suede Encrusted Mid-Heel Booties) which are 50% off right now — as well as the pink Melton Studio blazer and the Menswear Inspired Coat. I love a good try-on sesh! 🥰 #ad #whbmholidaystores #itsherhouse
Wishing you and your loved ones a very Merry Christmas! I hope it’s been a day filled with lots of love and joy. 🎄❤️ #merrychristmas #christmaslove

Our annual holiday photo.🎄 My little old man was so over it. I had to give him lots of neck and ear scratchies to get him to look up. 😄 I will always cherish these photos and moments with him in this apartment. I’m so happy to have him back in the city with me this week! Keep swiping to see our other holiday pics from the last few years here. 2019 is the only one we missed. I couldn’t find my Santa slippers. ☹️ #holidayphoto #lovehim #holidaydecor #holidaycard #christmastradition

Goodbye 2022 👋🏼 I’m so ready to close this chapter. These might be happy moments, but it was definitely one of the most difficult years for me in my personal life. I don’t think I’ve ever faced so much uncertainty and anxiety before, but I made it through little by little. ⁣
⁣
I still don’t have the clarity that I was hoping to have at this point, but I think this year really taught me about patience. It reminded me that things always have a way of falling into place — it just might not happen when we want it to. 2022 was filled with a lot of inner work, self-reflection and solitude, but I’m so grateful for the moments like this that reminded me of all the things I have to be grateful for. ⁣
⁣
As I look back on where I was at in January versus where I’m at now, I can see so much growth and improvement within myself. I’m going into 2023 with a much more positive mindset and I’m hopeful for what’s to come. I think that this new year is going to be filled with a lot of new beginnings for me and I’m trying to be at peace with wherever I end up next. 😌 ⁣
⁣
I wanted to say thank you to everyone who’s still here with me. I know my content has changed and my posting is very inconsistent compared to how it used to be. I always appreciate the love, support and encouraging words that you share no matter where I’m at in my journey. 😘 #goodbye2022 #yearlyrecap #lifechats #endofyear #yearinreview

I’m currently cozy in Connecticut, but I had to continue my NYE tradition of getting dressed up and having a mini Prosecco at home! 🥳⁣
⁣
What a year it has been. It’s tested me in more ways than one, but ultimately it only made me stronger and more resilient. It was a reminder for me that I can get through anything. ⁣
⁣
I am wishing all of you an abundance of health, love, happiness, opportunities and new beginnings in 2023! Hope you all have a fun and safe night. Cheers to a new chapter! Happy New Year! 🥂 #nye #newyearseve #cheers #nyestyle #happynewyear #2023 #goodbye2022

Happy 2023! I had the most relaxing weekend in Connecticut thanks to the best hosts. Good food, good wine, good company. Such a calming way to kick off this new year. 😌 I hope the first two days have been good to you! ⁣
⁣
I shared this on stories and had some great conversations about it, but wanted to share it here too — I started something called the two-minute rule. It’s supposed to help with procrastination and completing small tasks. This is the rule: if you can complete something in two minutes or less you do it NOW instead of putting it off. Over time, this is supposed to help you tackle the bigger things. ⁣
⁣
Does anyone else struggle with procrastination? If you do, try this and let me know if it helps! 🫶🏼 #2023 #newyear #connecticut #cozy #minigetaway

If the relationship between you and who you really are is primary to you — if feeling good matters most to you — then everything else will fall into place. ✨⁣
⁣
This is the energy I’m bringing for 2023. The relationship that I have with myself wavered a lot last year. Anxiety and sadness took over on most days and I lost sight of the things that truly made me happy and made me feel good. I want to be kinder to myself this year. I want to fall back in love with the little things that bring me joy and inner peace — running, reading, journaling, sitting in my solitude and hopefully another solo trip. 😌 #abrahamhicks #manifesting #selflove #innerpeace #affirmations

A few texts from people I love — fully inspired by @thecasaverde 🫶🏼 I loved the idea of this series so much and wanted to create my own version of it. ⁣
⁣
Something I’ve learned as I’ve gotten older is that every friendship has such a different dynamic. People show up for you in different ways. And I have really come to appreciate that. ⁣
⁣
All of these texts made me smile and I truly enjoyed putting this together. It was actually kind of therapeutic in a way. 😌 #texts #textsilove #momentsofmine #mypeople

I have a 7 year old niece! Happy Birthday to my forever munchkin, Mia. 🥳 She showed me what it meant to be a titi. Being an aunt has been one of the biggest blessings in my life. The years have gone by far too quickly, but I have loved watching her grow up. She’s so beautiful, kind, intelligent and brave. I love all of our fun and silly moments together. I love her adventurous spirit. Forever proud to be her auntie! She will be taller than me soon!🥰 #birthdaygirl #thisis7 #auntie #myniece #loveher #bestie

A little bit of my January camera roll so far 🫶🏼 It mostly consists of work content these days but here’s a few moments from the last two weeks. 🥰 I miss chatting with all of you! Tell me something good that happened to you recently.

Little by little I’m falling back in love with my life. 🫶🏼 Last year stole so much of my joy and I refuse to let that happen again. Things aren’t perfect by any means but I think all of my recent struggles have shown me that everything always has a way of working itself out. I’m learning to trust that more. When things fall apart just remember that it’s an opportunity for you to rebuild. Missed you! I hope January was good to you. ✨⁣
⁣
#loveyourlife #momentsofmine #motivationalreel #rebuild #2023energy
Don’t know if I did this right but I love this TikTok trend 😄Trying to have fun with content again! Reminder: Post what you want. Don’t overthink it. 🫶🏼 #albumcover

When I went to Amsterdam & Belgium back in 2019, I had no idea that would be my last solo trip for awhile. Words can’t fully express how difficult it’s been for me to not be able to travel as much as I did before. So much has changed in my life since then. I went without work for such a long time and I’ve been playing catch up ever since. Little by little, I’m getting back to where I need to be and I cannot wait for the day that I’m able to pack up and head back to Europe! I’m manifesting a trip to Portugal later this year — even if only for a short amount of time. And at some point I’d still love to do a month or two in Italy. ⁣
⁣
Life is wild. These last few years have taken me on an emotional rollercoaster. Just when I think I know what’s going to happen next the universe shows me it has other plans. But one thing that’s remained constant is the timing of it all. Little inconveniences have turned into blessings and it’s all reminded me that things always have a way of working out — even if it looks different than how we envisioned it’d be. 🤍 #lifechats #solotrip #solotravels #eurotrip #travelthrowback

A series of random moments from the last few weeks. One day continues to blur right into the next. I haven’t had much of a social life lately. Can someone please invite me to something fancy so I can get all dressed up? Thanks in advance. 😬 #cameraroll #photodump #lifelately

I’ve only posted 10 times on the feed so far this year. I remember the days when that would give me anxiety. But posting less has actually made me happier, if I’m being honest. ⁣It’s allowed me to release this immense amount of pressure that I used to put on myself when it came to social media. I think I’m still trying to figure out how I want to show up on here these days, but right now I’m enjoying more time offline. ⁣
⁣
Here’s a little bit of life lately: I took myself out on a solo Valentine’s Day date. I haven’t done this in months and it was so needed. I played pickleball for the first time for a feature we did for work. I went to an off-Broadway show. My 4 year old niece slept over for the first time (and kicked me all night 😂) I’ve been getting back into running and I have my first race in April. Struggling with it lately, but little by little I’m getting there. 🫶🏼#lifelately #solodate #momentsofmine #cameraroll #photodump #sliceoflife

I keep trying to remember to film more but here’s 21 seconds of February. 🫶🏼 ⁣
⁣
#lifelately #cameraroll #februarymoments #byefebruary #momentslikethese

She’s coming home. 😌 My mom’s surgery went really well yesterday. She’s experiencing some discomfort but other than that she’s doing great so far. It’s been such a high anxiety time as you can imagine so I am very thankful this part is behind us. We’ve got 6 weeks of recovery ahead — taking it all one day at a time. I’m happy that I’m here with her to help out as much as I can. Thank you again to everyone who has checked in and for all of the prayers and messages! It means more than you know. 🫶🏼 #mymama #loveher #wegotthis
I’m a little late but Happy International Women’s Day! Don’t forget to take up space and be exactly who you are 🫶🏼 #internationalwomensday #womensday #lovethem

Life has been an absolute whirlwind lately. I have so much to fill you in on. I’m not quite ready to share yet, but I will soon. ⁣For some good news — my mom’s recovery has been going great. The first week and a half was very tough but things are much better for her now. It’s such a relief to have the most difficult part behind us. ⁣
⁣
I spent 12 days in Jersey then came home and went straight to work. Haven’t had many calming moments lately, but I did attend a wonderful dinner last night with @visitnetherlands 🌷 It made me miss Amsterdam and traveling so much. I sat next to this amazing woman who reminded me that I’m doing better than I think I am. 🥹⁣
⁣
Here’s a little collection of photos from this month so far. 🫶🏼 #cameraroll #marchmoments #lifelately #sliceoflife #photodump

This city has forced me to grow in ways I could have never imagined. I think back to who I was when I first moved here at 34 and I don’t even recognize that version of myself anymore. Living alone has been one of the greatest joys and accomplishments of my life, but it’s also been extremely challenging. It’s heightened a lot of emotion for me, like loneliness and anxiety, but it’s also filled me with so much empowerment. There’s an interesting juxtaposition there — the way something can both fuel you and deplete you simultaneously. I sometimes feel that people who live alone don’t get enough credit. If you’re out here doing it, I see you! It’s not easy, but I’m proud of you. I’m proud of us. 🫶🏼 #dearnyc #lifechats #livingalone #lifeinnyc #nycrooftop

Went on a little brunch cruise around Manhattan on this gloomy morning. ☺️ I admittedly haven’t had much of a social life lately, so this was such a fun way to kick off the weekend. Definitely needed this! And I must do it again on a sunnier day. 🛳️ #brunchcruise #onaboat #itstheweekend #sailnyc

I did it! My first NYC race 🏃🏻‍♀️I’m so happy I finished it but this was a very tough one for me both physically and mentally. ⁣
⁣
The wind this morning was so brutal. I struggled a lot with my breathing right from the start, especially going up Cat Hill. And then at the halfway point my right hip started hurting. I pulled a muscle recently and thought it had gotten better but unfortunately the pain came back. I knew in order to make it through the second half I’d have to listen to my body and take it extremely slow. So I did. Right before the finish line — literally a few feet away — my right leg completely gave out and I fell to the ground. These two runners next to me were so wonderful and helped me get up and walk across the finish. ⁣
⁣
This is not how I envisioned my first race to go. I never experienced this on any of my runs before. So many emotions ran through me at the end but ultimately it seemed like the perfect representation of the way things have been happening in my life lately. I keep getting knocked down but I always get back up. And somehow I always find a way to push through, no matter what. I’m proud of myself for not giving up and seeing this goal all the way to the end. I’ll get ‘em next time. ⁣
⁣
A huge thank you to @bygracelee for pushing me and for cheering me on today. You inspire me with my running and I’m so proud of you. 🫶🏼 #runasone4m #centralpark #nyrr #runningjourney #getbackup

Easter Sunday 🌸 Such a fun day with the fam having lunch at Carmine’s & then going to see The Lion King — it was phenomenal! Highly recommend. Here’s a few snaps from the day. It’s always so chaotic when we’re all together, so I’ll take whatever I can get. 😄 Hope you’re all having a wonderful Easter! 🫶🏼#eastersunday #happyeaster #sundayfunday
Spring in NYC 🫶🏼 although it’s been feeling more like summer lately 😅 A few snaps from my work adventures around the city this week. #cameraroll #springinnyc #feelslikesummer

Kiko turned 13 today 🥹 This little boy has filled my life with so much love and happiness. We found each other shortly after my father’s cancer diagnosis and I swear he helped me get through it all. He changed my life. He’s been by my side through everything these last 13 years and I honestly don’t know what I’d do without him. Even though he didn’t move to NYC with me full time, I’ve enjoyed every moment I’ve spent with him here. He’s so special and I’m eternally grateful for him and his love. He’s my best friend. He’s my soul dog. Happy Birthday to my little muppet baby! 🥳 I love you so much! #birthdayboy #thisis13 #souldog #furbaby #dogmama #lovehim

LIFE UPDATE — I’m moving! 🫶🏼 ⁣
⁣
I wrote a very lengthy blog post today that I hope you’ll read. I’m sharing everything that led to this point with the move, the timing of it all, where I’m going, the new apartment — all of it. It’s been a lot to process and I think it still doesn’t feel real that I’m leaving the first home I ever got on my own and that I’m leaving New York — but I’m not going far. I’ve got two weeks left here and I know move out day will be really hard but I’m also looking forward to starting a new chapter. ⁣
⁣
“I walked through these doors as a 34 year old who was about to live on her own for the first time in the big city. It unequivocally changed me. It forced me to grow in ways I could have never imagined. This city kicked my ass an insane amount of times, but the resilience it instilled in me is something I’ll be forever grateful for. There were many moments when I was not sure if I’d be able stay in New York but by the grace of God I made it work for as long as I did. 5 years! It’s something to be proud of.⁣
⁣
I’m walking out of here at 39 as a completely different person, ready to embrace whatever lies ahead because I know I can do hard things. I’ve done them many times over. And I have to continuously remind myself of that when anxiety tries to get the best of me. ⁣
⁣
This chapter of life has been one I haven’t quite understood, but I think in the months and years ahead I’ll be able to look back on this time and it will all make sense. In my heart, it will always be New York or nowhere and I truly do hope that I can find my way back.⁣
⁣
If you’re currently going through a difficult time in your life or have been faced with uncertainty, I hope that in some small way my story can make you feel less alone and give you some hope that things will work themselves out. We might not always get what we want, but I do believe we get what we need. Just stay open. All these dark moments that we experience teach us so much, we just have to pay attention to the lessons.⁣
⁣
And I hope you always remember, it is never too late to start over.” ❤️ You can read more at natymichele.com (link in bio) #lifeupdate #lifechats #immoving #newchapter

10 more days until Hoboken becomes my new home. I was resistant to this change at first. It was really difficult for me to understand why after 5 years I was being pushed out of New York. But finally today, I had a moment by the water where I realized that this move is probably going to be the best thing for me and my mental health. I have been holding on to so much this past year and I’m slowly starting to let it all go. It’s still a process. This will all still be an adjustment for me. But being out here by the water — so close to my new home — I felt an inner calmness that I haven’t had in such a long time. And that’s really all I’ve been wanting. 🫶🏼 #hoboken #newhome #immoving #cityviews #innerpeace #lifechats

Happy 73rd Birthday to my beautiful and amazing mama! 🥳 I hope you never lose your spirit and desire to get up on the dance floor. It’s been a really tough year for you and seeing your strength and resilience has inspired me so much. You’ve taught me that I can get through anything life throws my way. I’m so thankful I get to call you my mom. These are just a handful of the many videos I have of you dancing and being silly and I will cherish them forever. Thank you for loving me and showing me that I can’t take myself too seriously. Love you!! 🥰 #birthdaygirl #mymama #thisis73 #loveher #bestfriend

Got the keys! 🔑 Officially moving in on Tuesday. I walked into the empty apartment yesterday and all the emotions hit me at once. There was definitely a moment where I wasn’t sure if I’d be able to find another place in time. And knowing I have one now has given me so much relief. I also freaked out a little bit and said am I really doing this?! ⁣
⁣
Part of me is excited and anxious for this new beginning. I know it will be a good change for me — probably one that I’ve needed for a long time. I’m simultaneously having such a hard time letting go of my apartment now and leaving behind my every day life in NYC. I will miss it terribly. But I know that season served it’s purpose. ⁣
⁣
The new apartment needs some love and I will give it that! It’s outdated, which is going to be a bit of an adjustment for me. But I know I will make it work over time. I keep reminding myself this is temporary. It’s a stepping stone to get me to wherever I’m supposed to be next. I shared this in my blog post recently and wanted to share it here too because I think it’s a good reminder. “I’ve realized that a lot of what we pray for comes to fruition but not necessarily in the ways we’re expecting.” — I got what I prayed for. It might look different but it is still a blessing. 🫶🏼 #lifechats #immoving #gotthekeys #newchapter #emptyapartment

Happy Mother’s Day to my incredible mama. 🫶🏼 Seeing how much she has been through in her life and the way she always pushes through and perseveres has been so inspiring to me. I’m extremely thankful for her support and unconditional love. I don’t know who I’d be without her! 

And Happy Mother’s Day to my beautiful sister. 💕 You’ve been such a wonderful mom to Mia and Layla. We are all so lucky to have you in our lives! #mothersday #mymama #sisterfriend #lovethem

I moved out of the first apartment I ever got on my own and I closed out a 5 year chapter in New York City. Goodbyes are never easy. I know change is necessary but I resist it sometimes. @roadwaymoving made such a difficult day go so smoothly.  I could not have done this without them. They carefully packed up the rest of my belongings and made sure everything was secure. My furry friends in the building came to say goodbye. The movers told me to sit down and relax but I have anxiety so I got up every few minutes. 😄 They disassembled and wrapped up all my furniture. They were so quick and efficient and I give them a lot of credit for all they do. I took one last look at my beautiful garden view. It was such a strange feeling to see the apartment completely empty. These walls held so much for me these last 5 years. But the closing of one door means that it’s time to step into some new. The movers finished loading the truck and they assembled all my furniture at the new place. I can’t thank @roadwaymoving enough for making this goodbye a little bit easier. 🫶🏼 #roadwaymoving #movewithroadway#movingvlog #lifeupdate #newchapter #goodbye

My first few days in Hoboken — lots of unpacking & cleaning, walks with Kiko, exploring and relaxing! ⁣
⁣
I shared this on stories but wanted to post it here too. I’ve already had several moments where I thought to myself “I didn’t realize how much I needed this.” I was so resistant to this change at first. But as much as I loved my apartment and living in NYC I don’t think I fully understood just how much anxiety I was carrying with me, especially this past year. Now that I’ve made the move and have gotten through the most difficult parts, my body has been in a more relaxed state and literally all of these emotions I’ve held on to are starting to lift away. Stress and anxiety are exhausting. I didn’t know how much I was holding on to until this week when I was able to start letting go. ⁣
⁣
We don’t realize what we need sometimes until we get it. And sometimes forced change turns out to be the best kind of change. Only time will tell how I feel about living in Hoboken but as of right now I believe it was the best thing for me. ⁣
⁣
I can’t thank everyone enough for all the supportive and encouraging messages — for cheering me on — for getting excited for me. You have no idea how much it means! 🫶🏼 #imoved #hoboken #lifelately #cameraroll #change #lifechats

This part of my life is called — peace. 😌 I can’t deny it. There’s been an inner calmness that I have felt ever since I moved to Hoboken. This place is growing on me more each day. Kiko loves it here. It’s been so much easier for my mom to come visit. I’m closer to my family. All of this makes me love it even more. I miss NYC and I think I always will but I am now understanding why my journey led me here. I’ll continue to be open to this change and see what it brings me! 🫶🏼 #lifechats #newchapter #hoboken #peacewithin #myjourney

Some snapshots from May 📸 This was such a transitional month for me. It truly changed everything. I remember where I was at both mentally and emotionally this time last year. I had no idea where I was going next. I still hadn’t found a job. There were so many unknowns and the uncertainty overwhelmed me on a daily basis. It was isolating. ⁣
⁣
Here I am a year later living in a new apartment in a new city. I’m working. I’m feeling fulfilled. I’m letting go. And all of the pieces are slowly coming back together. ⁣
⁣
So much can happen and change in a year. Our expectations won’t always align with our reality — but stay open! Sometimes what we end up getting is even better — even if might not seem that way at first. 🫶🏼 #cameraroll #lifelately #sliceoflife #maymoments #photodump #goodbyemay

Halfway through June. 🫶🏼 It’ll already be a month tomorrow since I moved to Hoboken. It’s wild how quickly time has been passing by. I’m still settling in. There’s been moments where I’ve felt really good about the move and my new home but simultaneously I’ve found myself missing the parts of my life that no longer exist. I think it’s ok to feel both things. And boy do I feel deeply — about everything.😄 Here’s some snaps from the month so far. Hope that June has been treating you well! #cameraroll #junemoments #lifelately #recap #photodump

My 4 year old niece took the photos of me 😭 Such a fun and special day with my girl! We had a “titi and Layla day” — went to the park, got our nails done, got ice cream, watched a movie and now we’re headed to dinner soon. This is definitely one of the best parts about living in Hoboken. I’m so much closer to have these kinds of moments with my nieces. 

Layla is the funniest person I know, truly. She had me laughing all day with the things she says — like how she wishes she was already in high school and how she doesn’t want me to get married. 😂 #loveher #myniece #auntielife #summerfun #mybestie

Continued my tradition of celebrating my dad — went for a run this morning & then took myself out to lunch. Father’s Day never gets easier, even after all of these years. It’s already been 13 without him. It’s difficult for me to allow myself to think of all the things he’s missed. I know he’s still with me always, but I don’t think I’ll ever get over the fact that he’s physically gone. He was an incredible father and I’m forever grateful that I had him in my life for almost 27 years. The lessons he taught me have stayed with me to this day — and his unconditional love is still around me. Happy Father’s Day to my angel 🫶🏼 love you and miss you all the days of my life. #fathersday #celebratingyou #myangel #loveyoudad #missingyoualways

Moments from the last few weeks 🫶🏼⁣ Haven’t shared one of these in awhile. 
⁣
#junemoments #cameraroll #lifelately

I’ve settled much more into Hoboken this past month and while I’ve had many moments of longing for what my life was like in NYC, I’ve also come to really appreciate where my path has taken me. It’s not always easy to accept your current circumstances, especially when the expectations you had do not align with your reality — but there is so much inner peace when you finally get to a place of acceptance and trust in your journey. 🫶🏼⁣

July has been all about reconnecting with myself again and focusing on the things that I can do to create healthier habits. And just like that, I’m 40 🥳 A new year & a new decade begins. It feels a bit surreal that this day is officially here. I had a lot of anxiety leading up to this birthday. It’s a strange feeling knowing that my 30s have now come to a close. They were without a doubt the best and most challenging years of my life. And now it’s time to say goodbye and welcome an entirely new chapter. ⁣
⁣
I am definitely not where I thought I’d be at 40 and if I’m being honest, that used to make me sad. But I really do believe I’m exactly where I’m supposed to be. All of the setbacks and detours have been such an integral part of my journey and story and I wouldn’t have it any other way. I have come so far from where I used to be and I’m proud of that. And I think my younger self would be proud of who she’s become. ⁣
⁣
I want to be in my “say yes” era for 40 — trying and doing new things, putting myself in different environments and opening myself up to new opportunities. No more playing small. No more doubting myself. I’m leaving that energy behind. It is never too late to be who you want to be. Do not put limitations on yourself. ⁣
⁣
I cannot wait to see what my 40s will bring. I’m embracing this new decade and hope it will fill my life with all the things I’m still hoping to receive. Cheers to another trip around the sun — she’s 40, flirty and thriving! 🫶🏼 #thisis40 #newdecade #itsmybirthday #chapter40 #birthdaygirl #scorpioseason ⁣

December 4th was the 12 year anniversary of when I first started my blog and began creating content on social media. I still remember where I was at in my life at that time. It was a year after getting laid off from my job and freshly grieving the loss of my dad. I had lost all sense of direction and felt like everything I knew about my life had suddenly been taken away. Little did I know that the very first blog post was about to redirect the entire course of my journey. ⁣
⁣
These last 12 years have brought me some of the most incredible opportunities that I never imagined would happen for me. I’ve worked with some of my dream brands, got featured in magazines and even starred in a commercial — memories that I will always⁣
cherish. And I’ve made some great friendships along the way. ⁣
⁣
But the best part? All of you. Truly. Building an online community is something that I’ve always been extremely grateful for. I have shared so much of my life with you (the good, the bad, the ugly) and many of you have done the same with me. There have been many moments where your encouragement and support has helped me feel less alone in the things I’ve gone through. And I can’t thank you enough for that. My content has changed significantly over the years — from fashion to solo travels to life chats & more — so if you’re still here with me just know how much I appreciate you. ⁣
⁣
I might not blog much anymore or create content on here as often as I used to, but I still love connecting and sharing stories and will continue to do so. Cheers to trying new things, stepping outside of our comfort zones, pursuing dreams and not letting the opinions of others hold us back from the things we really want. Love you! 🫶🏼 #anniversary #mystory #12years #thankyou #myjourney

⁣
I turned 40 this year and entered what I hope will be my best decade yet. There’s still so much space between where I am and where I want to be but I’m hopeful for what’s to come. ⁣
⁣
2023 was a little lonely at times but I sat in that solitude and it helped me recognize the things I still needed to work through. It taught me that sometimes I hold on to things that no longer serve me out of comfort or fear of change. ⁣
⁣
